    <bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
      <head>Historical Information
</head>
      <p>King William County was formed in 1701 from King and Queen County.    
</p>
      <p>Most records were destroyed by a courthouse fire on 17 January 1885. Only a few order books and deed books exist.
</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
      <head>Scope and Content
</head>
      <p>King William County (Va.) Chancery Decree, 1862.  Consists of a copy decree from the chancery cause John A. Smither and others vs. Adm. of C.C. Davis and others.  The document instructs James Green, Henry Corr, and James H. Johnson to divide the slaves of the estate of C.C. Davis among Ann E. Davis, Joseph A. Smither in right of his wife Elizabeth, William Davis, and Martin C. Davis. 
</p>
    </scopecontent>
